#compdef sisi
# =============================================================================
# sisi — frost-beta's "Semantic Image Search CLI tool" — a local,
#         offline image search tool that uses OpenAI's CLIP model
#         (running locally via @frost-beta/clip + MLX) to find
#         images by semantic similarity to a text query OR another
#         image.  Built on top of:
#           - @frost-beta/clip: local CLIP inference using Apple's
#             MLX framework (M-series chips) or fallback CPU
#           - @frost-beta/huggingface: model downloader for
#             huggingface CLIP weights
#           - cli-progress: progress bars during image-indexing
#             scans (one progress bar per ~1000 images while
#             extracting CLIP embeddings)
#           - clipanion: TypeScript class-based CLI framework
#         sisi works in two phases:
#           1. `sisi index <dir>` — scan directory tree for images,
#              compute CLIP embedding for each (512-dim or 1024-dim
#              vector depending on model), persist embeddings to
#              local SQLite database
#           2. `sisi search <query>` — encode query text (or image
#              URL) into CLIP embedding, find indexed images with
#              cosine similarity > threshold, display top N matches
#         Designed for users who want Google Photos-style "find
#         pictures of dogs" search WITHOUT uploading photos to
#         cloud — purely local, no Internet needed after model
#         download.  Particularly popular with privacy-focused
#         photographers and on-device-AI enthusiasts.
#
# Author:  frost-beta / @zcbenz (Cheng Zhao) — Electron co-creator
#          + former Microsoft Edge engineer; now independent on-
#          device AI tools developer.  Created sisi in 2024 as a
#          showcase of MLX-based local AI inference on Apple
#          Silicon.
# Source:  https://github.com/frost-beta/sisi
# CLI:     src/cli.ts (uses arcanis/clipanion for class-based
#                       command definitions + npkgz/cli-progress for
#                       progress-bar display during indexing)
# Library: npkgz/cli-progress
#          (":hourglass: easy to use progress-bar for command-line/
#           terminal applications" — npkgz's TypeScript-Node
#           progress-bar library with multi-bar support; the
#           TypeScript-Node parallel to Go's vbauerster/mpb R559
#           and Rust's indicatif R522 MultiProgress.)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 577+ stars on frost-beta/sisi (last pushed
#          2024-09); cli-progress itself is 1252+ stars on npkgz/
#          cli-progress (continuous development since 2017 by
#          Andi Dittrich at npkgz).
#
